text: It is! I find it one of the most rewarding things in my job. I can’t wait until there are servers in the world that use processors I helped design. I already find it really cool that most Arm servers will be running code that has been compiled with a compiler (GCC) I helped write, and running an Operating System kernel (Linux) my friends contributed to, it will be even better when I can order a processor online that goes fast because of decisions I’ve made!
Thats a great achievement I have never seen a arm processor run on a server, I have only heard of them on phones, what clock speed are they going to run on.

I always wondered how people write compilers I mean compiling all the code giving tokens removing spaces. I only have knowledge on the stages of compilation so I always wondered how long it would take to write the perfect code, I mean I can just barely write a program without using the internet
And that an amazing nave Zeus God of lightning I think I know why you guys chose that nave, is it because it's super fast
